-- Kyocera, Century Tokyo Leasing to Develop Solar Power Stations
-- B y   C h i s a k i   W a t a n a b e
-- 2012-08-09T07:41:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-09/kyocera-century-tokyo-leasing-to-develop-solar-power-stations.html
Kyocera Corp. (6971) , a Japanese solar-panel
maker, and  Century Tokyo Leasing Co. (8439)  will set up a solar power
plant joint venture in Japan with a plan to bring 70 megawatts
of capacity under development in the next three years.  The venture, with Century Tokyo taking an 81 percent stake
and Kyocera the rest, will begin developing 35 megawatts of
power stations by March 2013, the two said today in a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chisaki Watanabe in Tokyo at 
 cwatanabe5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
